/better-call-saul-season-5-photos-premiere-date/ |title=See first photos from 'Better Call Saul' season 5 |last=Snierson |first=Dan |date=November 20, 2019 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120165600/https://ew.com/tv/2019/11/20/better-call-saul-season-5-photos-premiere-date/ |archive-date=November 20, 2019 |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref> In the weeks prior to the premiere, AMC had run a ''Breaking Bad'' marathon leading into the AMC premiere showing of ''[[El Camino: A Breaking Bad Movie]]'' as lead-in to ''Better Call Saul''{{'}}s fifth season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2020/01/07/breaking-bad-movie-amc-premiere-date-full-series-marathon/ |title=Breaking Bad Movie Gets AMC Premiere Date, Following a Full Series Marathon |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |date=January 7, 2020 |website=TVLine |access-date=January 7, 2020}}</ref> Regarding the decision to air the fifth season nearly a year and a half after the fourth, Sarah Barnett, the president of the entertainment networks group at AMC Networks, said the long hiatus was \"driven by talent needs, which we would not override if it would result in a worse show.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/04/killing-eve-amc-networks-bbc-america-strategy.html |title=Why AMC Networks Is Betting So Heavily on Killing Eve |last=Adalian |first=Josef |date=April 5, 2019 |website=[[Vulture.com|Vulture]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190409060215/https://www.vulture.com/2019/04/killing-eve-amc-networks-bbc-america-strategy.html |archive-date=April 9, 2019 |access-date=April 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOutside the U.S. in certain international markets, like previous seasons, season 5 is released on [[Netflix]] with episodes available the day after the episodes are broadcast on AMC.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/news/better-call-saul-season-5-netflix-release-schedule-02-2020/ |title=\u2018Better Call Saul\u2019 Season 5 Netflix Release Schedule |last=Moore |first=Kasey |date=February 23, 2020 |website=What's On Netflix |access-date=February 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nThe fifth season of ''Better Call Saul'' has received critical acclaim. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the season has an approval rating of 99% based on 33 reviews, with an average rating of 8.67/10. The website's critical consensus is, \"Grounded by Bob Odenkirk's endlessly nuanced, lived-in performance, ''Better Call Saul''{{'}}s fifth season is a darkly funny, vividly realized master class in tragedy.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/better_call_saul/s05 |title=Better Call Saul: Season 5 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |access-date=March 30, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the season has a score of 92 out of 100 based on 16 critics, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/better-call-saul/season-5 |title=Better Call Saul: Season 5 |website=[[Metacritic]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207062017/https://www.metacritic.com/tv/better-call-saul/season-5 |archive-date=February 7, 2020 |access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nKelly Connolly of ''[[TV Guide]]'' gave it 4.5/5 stars and wrote, \"This is why ''Better Call Saul'' is better at being a prequel than other prequels are: It understands that the tragedy of fate is baked into the story.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/better-call-saul-review-jimmy-becomes-saul-goodman-season-5/ |title=Better Call Saul Review: Jimmy Becomes Saul Goodman in a Fantastically Devastating Season 5 |last=Connolly |first=Kelly |date=February 6, 2020 |website=[[TV Guide]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206201012/https://www.tvguide.com/news/better-call-saul-review-jimmy-becomes-saul-goodman-season-5/ |archive-date=February 6, 2020 |access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Collider (website)|Collider]]'', Adam Chitwood gave it a perfect 5/5 star review, stating \"''Better Call Saul'' is revealing itself to be a possibly even better series [than ''Breaking Bad''], and one with more nuance. In addition to the thematic complexity, the direction and execution of this series is unparalleled by anything on television right now.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://collider.com/better-call-saul-season-5-review/ |title='Better Call Saul' Season 5 Review: Saul Goodman Finally Steps into the Spotlight |last=Chitwood |first=Adam |date=February 5, 2020 |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206141549/https://collider.com/better-call-saul-season-5-review/ |archive-date=February 6, 2020 |access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Notelist ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.amc.com/shows/better-call-saul|''Better Call Saul''}} \u2013 official site\n* {{IMDb episodes|3032476|Better Call Saul}}\n\n{{Better Call Saul}}\n\n[[Category:2020 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:Better Call Saul|Season 5]]\n", "name_user": "Billmckern", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEpisodes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Better_Call_Saul_(season_5)"}
{"title_page": "Limbdi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n<!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Indian cities]] for details -->{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Limbdi\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = Taluka\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Gujarat#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Gujarat, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|22|34|06.5|N|71|47|41.8|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Gujarat]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Surendranagar district|Surendranagar]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 53\n| population_total        = 42,769\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]], [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = [http://www.citypincode.in/GUJARAT/SURENDRA_NAGAR/Limbdi_PINCODE 363421]\n| registration_plate      =GJ 13\n| website                 = {{URL|gujaratindia.com}} \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Limbdi''' is a taluka with [[municipality]] in [[Surendranagar district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Gujarat]].<ref>https://surendranagardp.gujarat.gov.in/surendranagar/english/jillavishe/limbadi.htm</ref> With the construction of a majestic BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Temple in May 2010, Limbdi has become one of the most popular pilgrimage centers of Vaishnavaits world over.<ref>http://www.baps.org/Global-Network/India/Limbdi.aspx</ref>\n\n==History==\n{{Main|Limbdi State}}\nThe area formed a part of the 9-gun [[salute state]] during the [[British Raj]], when it was governed by members of a [[Jhala (clan)|Jhala]] dynasty.<ref>{{cite book |title=Sovereignty, Power, Control: Politics in the States of Western India, 1916-1947 |first=John |last=McLeod |publisher=BRILL |year=1999 |isbn=9789004113435 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jXpzWlPpE1cC&pg=PA9 |pages=8\u20139}}</ref>\n\n===Limbdi Satyagrah===\n{{unreferenced section|date=February 2014}}\nDuring the Satyagraha, the people of Limbdi formed a \"[[Praja Mandal]]\" on 24 December 1938, which caused friction between the king and the people of Limbdi. In 1939, a conference was held by \"Praja Mandal\", which the king did not like and he created a huge uproar at the conference. Many people were wounded during this incident. Many people felt disheartened and started migrating from Limbdi to other cities.\n\nIn 1940, after death of Sir Dolatsingh, Sir Digvijay became the ruler. He could rule for only four months, as he died shortly after his coronation. The last ruler of Limbdi was his son, Sir Chhatrapalsingh, from 1941 to 1948. After independence, Limbdi state was merged with Union of India.\n\n==Education==\nLady Wellingdon Girls School, now Municipal School number 3, was established in Limbdi on 1 March 1859, at a time when India had few girls' schools even in urban areas.{{citation needed|date=February 2014}} It is now a co-educational school.\n\n==Geography==\nLimbdi is located at {{Coord|22.57|N|71.8|E|}}.<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/9/Limbdi.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Limbdi]</ref> It has an average elevation of 53&nbsp;metres (173&nbsp;feet).\n\nLimbdi is located on NH-8,101&nbsp;km from [[Ahmedabad]].\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2001}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Limbdi had a population of 40,067. Males constitute 52% of the population and females 48%. Limbdi has an average literacy rate of 70%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 78%, and female literacy is 62%. In Limbdi, 12% of the population is under 6 years of age.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citypincode.in/GUJARAT/SURENDRA_NAGAR/Limbdi_PINCODE |title=Limbdi Pincode |publisher=citypincode.in |date= |accessdate=2014-05-19}}</ref>\n\n==Points of Interest==\n* BAPS Swaminarayan mandir, Limbdi <ref>http://download.baps.org/photos/2010limbdimandir.zip</ref>\n* Ramakrishna Mission, Limbdi<ref>http://rkmlimbdi.in</ref>\n* Shri Jagdish Ashram, Limbdi [of Jagannatah tirtha swamiji]<ref>http://jagdishashramlimbdi.org</ref> \n* Shree Kabir Ashram, Limbdi, and Kabir temple, located little far from the ashram<ref>http://www.kabiryogashram.org</ref>\n* Raj Rajeshwar Dham (Tridev temple), Jakhan is located nearby, easterly. The temple complex is built on a hundred-acre piece of land, the initial acreage donated by the people (Lalubha Madarsinh zala, Andubha zala, Jitubha zala) of Jakhan Village. This place is the headquarters of Life mission society which has a global network. The centre offers many facilities.<ref>http://www.lifemission.org</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.divyabhaskar.co.in/article/GUJ-narendramath-became-swami-vivekananda-in-gujarat-2609845.html Divya Bhaskar - Narendra became Vivekananda in Gujarat]\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Surendranagar district]]\n[[Category:Former capital cities in India]]\n[[Category:Taluka of Surendranagar]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n<!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Indian cities]] for details -->{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Limbdi\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = Taluka\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Gujarat#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Gujarat, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|22|34|06.5|N|71|47|41.8|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Gujarat]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Surendranagar district|Surendranagar]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 53\n| population_total      